# =============================================================================
# .gitignore for {{AGENT_NAME}} — a Hermes Telegram librarian
# =============================================================================
# The repo directory IS HERMES_HOME, so everything Hermes generates at runtime
# lands at the repo root. That runtime state is per-machine and must never be
# committed. What IS tracked: SOUL.md, README.md, config.yaml, hooks/, skills/,
# scripts/, .example files.
# =============================================================================

# --- Secrets (NEVER commit) --------------------------------------------------
# auth.json holds OpenAI Codex OAuth tokens + optional GitHub Copilot PAT.
# .env holds TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN, TELEGRAM_ALLOWED_USERS, OPENAI_API_KEY, etc.
auth.json
auth.lock
.env

# --- Hermes runtime state (per-machine, regenerated each session) -----------
*.pid                       # gateway.pid and similar
gateway_state.json
channel_directory.json
state.db                    # SQLite session store
state.db-*                  # SQLite WAL / shm sidecars
sessions/                   # per-conversation JSONL logs
memories/                   # Hermes long-term memory
cache/                      # Hermes model/response caches
sandboxes/                  # tool sandbox scratch dirs
logs/                       # hook + gateway logs
platforms/                  # per-platform pairing + rate-limit state
models_dev_cache.json
ollama_cloud_models_cache.json
.skills_prompt_snapshot.json
audio_cache/                # local voice cache (if materialized in-repo)
image_cache/                # local image cache (if materialized in-repo)
cron/                       # per-agent cron state

# --- OS / editor junk --------------------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
*.swp
*~

# --- Python ------------------------------------------------------------------
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.venv/
